The spearphishing attack (T1566) was successfully simulated using MITRE Caldera. Wazuh detected key indicators such as malicious links and suspicious PowerShell execution. Alerts were generated in real time, demonstrating effective monitoring. However, some attack stages, particularly payload execution, were not detected, highlighting gaps in detection rules. These gaps suggest the need for improved log analysis and rule tuning. Overall, the SOC environment showed moderate effectiveness in detecting phishing attacks but requires enhancement to ensure complete coverage of advanced adversary techniques.
